 by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Brace was born in 1400, in England, United Kingdom. He married Mrs. William Brace about 1424, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1400–":"1400–Surnud","1402–Female":"1402–Surnud","1425–Female":"1425–Surnud","1400–Male":"1400–Surnud","1425":"1425","1402":"1402","1400":"1400","about 1424":"umbes 1424","Abt 1425":"umbes 1425","England":"England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hanbury, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Hanbury, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1400–":"1400–Kuollut","1402–Female":"1402–Kuollut","1425–Female":"1425–Kuollut","1400–Male":"1400–Kuollut","1425":"1425","1402":"1402","1400":"1400","about 1424":"noin 1424","Abt 1425":"noin 1425","England":"England","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hanbury, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Hanbury, Worcestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1400–":"1400–Décédé","1402–Female":"1402–Décédée","1425–Female":"1425–Décédée","1400–Male":"1400–Décédé","1425":"1425","1402":"1402","1400":"1400","about 1424":"environ 1424","Abt 1425":"environ 1425","England":"Angleterre","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Hanbury, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Hanbury, Worcestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William Brace est né en 1400, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a épousé Mrs. William Brace environ 1424, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"1400–":"1400–Verstorben","1402–Female":"1402–Verstorben","1425–Female":"1425–Verstorben","1400–